### 3. `index.html` (Simple GitHub Pages Site)

Save this as `index.html` in the root. It will work automatically if you enable GitHub Pages on the repo.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Coherence Pump</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; background: #0a0a0a; color: #ddd; max-width: 720px; margin: 40px auto; padding: 20px; line-height: 1.6; }
        h1 { color: #7dd3fc; }
        a { color: #7dd3fc; }
        .card { background: #111; padding: 24px; border-radius: 12px; margin: 24px 0; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Coherence Pump</h1>
    <p>A multi-scale dynamical system exploring <strong>convergence + polarization</strong> through a three-layer quaternion graph flow model.</p>

    <div class="card">
        <h2>What is this?</h2>
        <p>The Coherence Pump models how systems can converge toward higher coherence while simultaneously differentiating across scales. It features recursive contraction, horocycle-style averaging, emergent behavior, and coherence-gated polarization.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h2>Repository</h2>
        <p><a href="https://github.com/yourusername/coherence-pump">github.com/yourusername/coherence-pump</a></p>
        <p>Includes the full simulation, animation script, and logged outputs.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h2>Quick Start</h2>
        <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/yourusername/coherence-pump.git
cd coherence-pump
pip install -r requirements.txt
python simulation.py</code></pre>
    </div>

    <footer style="margin-top: 60px; font-size: 0.9em; color: #666;">
        Built with Grok • Experimental framework exploring recursive coherence and multi-scale dynamics
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
